@Node Main "MusicBox.guide"

MusicBox - English Documentation

@Next "Information"


This is the documentation for MusicBox, the most powerful CD player for
Amiga computers with SCSI controller!


@{" Information                  " Link "Information"  }   Information

@{" The Installation             " Link "Installation" }   Installation of MusicBox

@{" The User interface           " Link "GUI"          }   The user interface

@{" The Menus                    " Link "Menus"        }   The menus

@{" The ToolTypes and Arguments  " Link "Startup"      }   MusicBox startup


@{" The ARexx-Port               " Link "ARexx"        }   ARexx port



@{" Copyright                    " Link "Copyright"    }   Copyright-Information
@EndNode

@Node "Information"

MusicBox is a player for audio-CDs in SCSI CDROM drives.


Features:
- Catalog:
  MusicBox can catalogize an unlimited count of CDs. Once a CD is
  catalogized, MusicBox identifies the disc and displays the current
  title. You can manage the full catalog of all catalogizes CD with
  the program "Catalog".

- Display options:
  MusicBox can show the playing time of a CD in minutes/seconds/frames,
  hex address, precent or megabytes from the beginning of the current track,
  the beginning of the CD or to the end of the track or the CD.
  MusicBox displays also the status of the drive, the SCSI bus, the CD type,
  audio channels, eject lock status, etc.

- Remote control by a joystick
  All important functions of MusicBox can be easily remote controlled by
  a joystick connected to port B. MusicBox offers two different joystick
  command sets.

- Automatic CD type recognition
  MusicBox automatically recognizes the type of the inserted CD

- Direct selection of the position within a track by prop gadget

- Volume control (if supported by CD-ROM drive)

- Redefine audio channels (if supported by CD-ROM drive),
  for example play the left audio track on the right speaker...

- ARexx-Port


Hardware requirements:
- Amiga with Kickstart 2.04+
- 1 MByte memory, more recommended
- SCSI controller which supports SCSI direct commands

Software requirements:
- Workbench 2.0, 2.1 recommended for locale support
@EndNode


@Node "Installation"

Installation

Start "Install" from Workbench or CLI/Shell and follow the instructions.

After installation, add the following lines to S:User-Startup
Assign MusicBox: <dir>
Assign AudioCD:  <dir>/AudioCD
SetENV CDROM_DEVICE=<device name>
SetENV CDROM_UNIT=<unit number>

where <dir> is the directory you have installed MusicBox in.
<device name> is the name of your SCSI device (e.g. "scsi.device") and
unit number is the SCSI ID of your CD-ROM drive.

If you do not add the SetENV lines, you can specify the ToolTypes DEVICE=
and UNIT= for MusicBox.

If you do not know your SCSI settings, read Inquiry.txt!

IMPORTANT NOTE:
If you set CDROM_DEVICE and CDROM_UNIT, the ToolTypes will be ignored!
@EndNode


