@EndNode


@Node "§1"

The track display

The track display displays the number of the current track
@EndNode


@Node "§2"

The position display

The position display show the position of the laser on the CD.
The position is relative to the beginning of the CD, the beginning of
the track (default) or the end of the CD or the end of the track dependent
on the "Preferences" menu settings.
The format of the position can be minutes/seconds/frames (default),
hex address, megabytes or precent dependent of the "Preferences" menu
settings.

To modify the settings, use the following menus:

@{"Preferences/Display" Link "Preferences@Display"}
@{"Preferences/Format " Link "Preferences@Format"}

Note:
The current system time is displayed, if there is no audio-CD inserted.
@EndNode


@Node "§3"

The Title Selection Field

Here you can select a title of the current CD.
By clicking a title once, the title will be activated and written into
the text field below the selection field, where the title can be edited
(see @{"Title Editing Field" Link "§42"})
Double-clicking a title will start playing the title.

@EndNode


@Node "§4"

The left audio channel symbol

This symbol displays, which channel of the CD will be heard
on the left audio channel.

L  = left channel (default)
R  = right channel
II = both channels
   = none

The setting can be modified by the @{"Channel Gadget L" Link "§16"}.

@EndNode


@Node "VL"

Volume display for the left channel

This display shows the volume on the left channel (0 to 255).

@EndNode


@Node "§5"

The right audio channel symbol

This symbol displays, which channel of the CD will be heard
on the right audio channel.

L  = left channel
R  = right channel (default)
II = both channels
   = none

The setting can be modified by the @{"Channel Gadget R" Link "§31"}.

@EndNode


@Node "VR"

Volume display for the right channel

This display shows the volume on the right channel (0 to 255).

@EndNode


@Node "§6"

The status display

The status display shows the current status of MusicBox:

Symbols:
- Stand-by
- Play
- Stop
- Wind
- Rewind
- Auto-play (MusicBox pauses 4-5 seconds before starting play)
- Positioning

@EndNode


@Node "§7"

The SCSI status display

The SCSI status display shows the status of the SCSI bus:

Symbols:
- Okay (Symbol with title "SCSI")
- Stand-by ("SCSI" without symbol)
- Error ("SCSI ERR")

@EndNode


@Node "§8"

The joystick display

The joystick displays shows the command set of the joystick control feature:

Symbols:
- I (command set one)
- II (command set two)
- none (joystick control feature turned off)

See @{"Preferences/Joystick" Link "Preferences@Joystick"} for more information on the joystick control feature.

@EndNode


@Node "§9"

The auto-play symbol

If auto-play is turned on, MusicBox starts playing after a
new CD is inserted.

To activate/deactivate this feature, use:
@{"Preferences/Auto functions/Auto-play" Link "Preferences@AF@AutoPlay"}

Note: MusicBox waits 4-5 seconds before auto-playing a CD to give
      an ISO9660 filesystem time to examine the CD.

@EndNode


@Node "§10"

The auto-repeat symbol

If auto-repeat is turned on, MusicBox starts playing track 1, if playing
has stopped at the end of the current CD.

To activate/deactivate this feature, use:
@{"Preferences/Auto functions/Auto-repeat" Link "Preferences@AF@AutoRepeat"}
@EndNode


@Node "§11"

The eject-lock symbol

This symbol shows the status of the eject-lock:

To activate/deactivate eject-lock, use:
@{"Eject Lock" Link "§38"}
@EndNode


@Node "§12"

The CD-inserted symbol

This symbol show, whether a data or audio CD is inserted or not.
@EndNode


@Node "§13"

The CD type symbol

This symbol show the type of the current CD: data or audio.
@EndNode


@Node "§14"

The catalogized symbol

This symbol shows whether the current CD has been catalogized or not.
@EndNode


@Node "§15"

The play/pause button

This button starts playing the current CD. If MusicBox is already playing,
clicking this button pauses playing until the button is clicked again.
@EndNode


@Node "§16"

The channel selection for the left audio channel

Here you can select which channel of the CD will be played on the left
audio channel: The left (default), right, both or none.

Note:
This feature is not supported by all CD-ROM drives.

@EndNode


@Node "§17"

The number buttons

Here you can enter a track number. The button @{"OK" Link "§33"} starts playing
the entered track. The key "#" clears the {"Input field" Link "§40"}.

Note:
Instead of clicking on the number buttons, you can of course use the
keyboard and enter the numbers.
@EndNode


@Node "§18"

The close button

Clicking this button iconifies MusicBox, the program will not be ended.
To quit MusicBox, use @{"Project/Quit MusicBox" Link "Project@Quit"}

Note:
MusicBox can be configured to quit byclicking on the button instead of
iconifying. See @{"ToolTypes" Link "Startup"} for more details.

@EndNode


@Node "§20"

The stop button

This button stops playing.

@EndNode


@Node "§31"

The channel selection for the right audio channel

Here you can select which channel of the CD will be played on the right
audio channel: The left, right (default), both or none.

Note:
This feature is not supported by all CD-ROM drives.

@EndNode


@Node "§21"

The volume control for the left audio channel

Here you can modify the volume of the left audio channel.
If the field "L=R" is activated, the volume of the right channel
will be set to the same value.


Note:
Volume changing by software is not supported by all CD-ROM drives.

@EndNode


@Node "§25"

The "L=R" field

If this field is activated, the changing of the volume of one audio channel
will set the volume of the other channel to the same value.

See also
@{"Volume control for the left audio channel " Link "§21"}
@{"Volume control for the rught audio channel" Link "§36"}
for more details on changing the volume.

@EndNode


@Node "§29"

The rewind button

Clicking this button causes MusicBox to starts decreasing the
current position.
To continue playing, click on @{"Play/Pause" Link "§15"}.


Note:
You can also use the @{"Position Gadget" Link "§35"} to change the current
position.

@EndNode


@Node "§30"

The wind button

Clicking this button causes MusicBox to starts increasing the
current position.
To continue playing, click on @{"Play/Pause" Link "§15"}.


Note:
You can also use the @{"Position Gadget" Link "§35"} to change the current
position.

@EndNode


@Node "§33"

The OK Button

The track number entered by @{"Number buttons" Link "§17"} or the keyboard
will be played.


Note:
Instead of clicking the OK button, you can also use the RETURN key.

@EndNode


@Node "§34"

The ? Button

MusicBox starts playing a track, which is chosen randomly.
@EndNode


@Node "§35"

The Position Gadget

You can modify the current position within the current track by moving this
prop gadget. This is usually more comfortable than using the wind/rewind
buttons.

@EndNode


@Node "§36"

The volume control for the right audio channel

Here you can modify the volume of the right audio channel.
If the field "L=R" is activated, the volume of the left channel
will be set to the same value.


Note:
Volume changing by software is not supported by all CD-ROM drives.

@EndNode


@Node "§37"

The Eject Button

Clicking this button ejects the an inserted CD, if ejecting is not permitted
by the @{"Eject lock" Link "§38"}.


Note:
Ejecting by software is not supported by all CD-ROM drives.

@EndNode


@Node "§38"

The Eject-lock Button

Here you can forbid or permit the ejection of the CD. You can see the
status of the eject-lock at the @{"Eject-lock symbol" Link "§11"}.


Note 1:
Eject-lock forbids/permits ejection by clicking the Eject button AND
the button on the drive.

Note 2:
Ejecting by software is not supported by all CD-ROM drives.

@EndNode


@Node "§39"

The - Button

Clicking this button causes MusicBox to play the previous track.

@EndNode


@Node "§40"

The Title Editing Field

Here you can enter a track number using the keyboard or the @{"number buttons" Link "§17"}
The RETURN key or the @{"OK button" Link "§33"} starts playing the entered track
@EndNode


@Node "§41"

The + Button

Clicking this button causes MusicBox to play the next track.

@EndNode


@Node "§43"

The Playing Mode Button

The you can select whether MusicBox should play the tracks on the current
CD number by number or randomly.

@EndNode


@Node "Preferences@Display"

Der Menüpunkt Preferences/Display

Here you can choose what to display in the @{"Position Display" Link "§2"}:

- Time from beginning of the current track (default)
- Time from beginning of the disc
- Time to the end of the current track
- Time to the end of the disc

@EndNode


@Node "§42"

The Title Editing Field

Here you can modify the title selected in the @{"Title Selection Field" Link "§3"}.


Important Note:
End your input by pressing the RETURN key!

@EndNode


@Node "§100"

The Toshiba-3401B symbol

If you CD-ROM drive is a Toshiba 3401B, a small T is displayed here.

@EndNode


