@Node "Project@SavePreferences"

The "Save preferences" Item

This item saves the preferences of MusicBox.

Note:
Title catalogs will automatically be saved when changed.
So "Save preferences" is not necessary.

@EndNode


@Node "Project@LoadPreferences"

The "Load preferences" Item

This item loads previously saved preferences of MusicBox.

@EndNode


@Node "Project@Setup printer"

The "Setup printer" Item

This item starts SYS:Prefs/Printer to modify the printer preferences.

@EndNode


@Node "Project@Print"

The "Printer" Item

This item prints the catalog of the current CD.

@EndNode


@Node "Project@About"

The "About MusicBox" Item

This item shows information about MusicBox and your hardware.
@EndNode


@Node "Project@Iconify"

The "Iconify" Item

This item iconifies MusicBox.

@EndNode


@Node "Project@Help"

The "Help" Item

This item shows this AmigaGuide file.

@EndNode


@Node "Project@Quit"

The "Quit MusicBox" Item

This item ends MusicBox.

@EndNode


@Node "Preferences@AF@AutoRepeat"

The "Auto-repeat" Item

This item turns Auto-repeat feature on or off.

@EndNode


@Node "Preferences@AF@AutoPlay"

The "Auto-play" Item

This item turns Auto-play feature on or off. Auto-play means that
MusicBox automatically starts playing a CD when inserted.


Note:
MusicBox wait ca. 5 seconds before starting to play to give a
ISO9660-FileSystem-Handler enough time to examine the CD.
@EndNode


@Node "Preferences@AF@GH"

The "Load full catalog quietly" Item

If activated, MusicBox automatically starts the program "Catalog" in
background, which gives you the possiblity to manage all catalogs.
Otherwise, Catalog is started, when you select Information/Display full
catalog.
Activating this item speeds up loading the catalog, but also requires
memory.

@EndNode


@Node "Preferences@AF@Flush"

The "Flush resources" Item

Activating this item causes MusicBox to flush all resources (fonts,
libraries, etc). when quitting.
This is useful for program development but not useful for normal usage.
So in most cases, you do not need to activate this feature.

@EndNode


@Node "Preferences@AF@KS"

The "Auto-save catalog" Item

If activated, MusicBox automatically saves an edited CD-ROM catalog without
confirmation. Otherwise, MusicBox asks you if you want to save it.

@EndNode


@Node "Preferences@Format"

The Format Menu

Here you can select the format for the @{"Position Display" Link "§2"}:
- Time in mins/secs/frames
  (default, like a normal CD player)
- 32-Bit Address
  Sector number as 32-bit number. (1 sector = 2048 bytes)
- Percent
- Megabytes
  like 32-Bit Address, but converted to Megabytes and decimal)

@EndNode


@Node "Preferences@Joystick"

The Joystick Menu

Here you can select the command set for the Joystick Control feature:
- Off (no joystick support)
- Level I (normal joystick support)
- Level II (extended joystick support)

Level I:

Play/Pause:
  Move stick forward for ca. 1 second

Stop:
  Move stick back for ca. 1 second

Next track:
  Move stick left for ca. 1 second

Previous track:
  Moe stick right for ca. 1 second

Note: In Level I, the fire button has no function


Level II:

Play/Pause:
  Move stick forward and press fire

Stop:
  Move stick backward and press fire

Next track:
  Move stick right and press fire

Previous track:
  Move stick left and press fire

Volume control:
  Move stick to upper left corner to decrease or upper right corner to
  increase volume and press fire until volume level is reached.

Wind/Rewind:
  Move stick to lower left corner for rewind, lower right corner for wind.
  Press fire and release stick.
  Wait until the track position is reached.
  Move stick forward and press fire. (like Play/Pause)

@EndNode


@Node "Info@Kat"

The "Load full catalog" Item

This item starts the program "Catalog", which lets you manipulate the
full CD catalog.

@EndNode


@Node "Info@ACD"

The "About current CD" Item

This item shows information about the current CD.

@EndNode


@Node "Info@ADr"

The "About CD-ROM-drive" Item

This item shows information about your CD-ROM-drive.

@EndNode


@Node "Startup"

ToolTypes and Arguments of MusicBox


Starting MusicBox:

MusicBox can be started from Workbench or CLI/Shell.

Arguments for CLI/Shell call:

-q oder QUIET:
  MusicBox starts iconified; useful for Start in S:User-Startup etc.

-u oder US:
  MusicBox ignores locale settings and starts with English user interface.

-l oder LOWRES:
  This option forces MusicBox to use a resolution of 640x256, although
  a higher resolution can be used.

-r oder NOREQ:
  MusicBox does not open an error requester, if the CD-ROM-drive is
  not available. This is useful when MusicBox is automatically startet,
  although the CD-ROM-driver is turned off.

-i oder IGNORETOOLTYPES:
  All ToolTypes entries will be ignored.


ToolTypes entries

QUIET=ON|OFF
  MusicBox starts iconified (ON) or not iconified (OFF)

FASTEXIT=ON|OFF
  MusicBox will quit, when clicked on the close button (ON) or
  be iconified (OFF)

US=ON|OFF
  ON:  Locale will be ignored
  OFF: MusicBox uses locale

LOWRES=ON|OFF
  see -l/LOWRES

DEVICE=<device>
  Sets the name of the SCSI device. See Inquiry.txt for more details.

  Note: If the is an environment variable CDROM_DEVICE, the variable
  will be used and the DEVICE= entry will be ignored!

UNIT=<unitnummer>
  Sets the unit number of the CD-ROM drive. See Inquiry.txt for more details.

  Note: If the is an environment variable CDROM_UNIT, the variable
  will be used and the UNOT= entry will be ignored!

AREXXPORT=<name>
  Sets the name of the ARexx port

@EndNode


@Node "ARexx"

The ARexx port


Commands:

iconify
  iconifies MusicBox

uniconify
  uniconifies MusicBox

click [Button]
  Simulates a click on a button:

  play {n} = Play/Pause
             n is an optional argument for the track to play
  stop     = Stop
  eject    = Eject
  lock     = Eject-lock
  next     = Play next track (+ button)
  prev     = Play previous track (- button)
  rnd      = Play random track (? button)

archive
  Loads the program "Catalog"

about {cd|drive}
  <without Arguments  see (@{"Project/About MusicBox" Link  "Project@About MusicBox"})
  cd                  see {@{"Information/About CD" Link    "Info@ACD"})
  drive               see (@{"Information/About CD-ROM-drive" Link "Info@ADr"})


Note:
  The name of the ARexx port can be changed:
  See @{"ToolTypes" Link "Startup"} for more details.

@EndNode


